  "text": "Ground truth secondary structure assignments for each protein chain were obtained using the DSSP program [CITATION_1] . In the current study, the eight DSSP output classes are mapped to three states as follows: H={H,G,I}, E={E,B}, T={T,S,-}, where '-' denotes 'other'. This conversion is recommended as being a conservative approach [CITATION_2] . This resulted in 20% of residues assigned to class E (βstrands), 33% of residues assigned to class H (α-helices), and the remaining 47% of residues assigned to class T (loops, turns, or non-regular structure).",
